description:
This has been a struggle to acquire and process. 

My original plan was to go deep on this target at high resolution.. However, during the time I had good seeing, the moon was large and bright and couldn't shoot any broad band (ended up shooting M1) and everytime I tried shooting L on this target, the seeing was terrible and I had to eke out subs out of multiple nights.  

The color data had horrible gradients as well as I did bad framing (or may be it was mirror flop and I had badly framed images as well that had to be discarded).  I pushed the processing as much as I could but it has fallen well short of my target. I will keep trying to collect data but the forecast isn't looking good and the target is going to hit meridian early before long (and I cant shoot past it).

The stars are big and fluffy.. cant do much about up ... If only I had some good seeing on moonless nights.


Version B: Collected more L subs and threw out a bunch of less quality subs
L - 162*3 mins
R/G/B - 50/60/55 * 3min
title: NGC7331: Deer lick Group
